Author: jl777c#5810
Content: looking at orderbooks and depth, if cross chain arbitrage was possible, the binance price would go to 1100, but this assumes there is nobody who is waiting to buy until after the exchanges open. clearly there are those waiting to deposit and sell, but for those expecting a 50% correction, that doesnt seem likely. current CMC price is most likely +/- 5% from the price it will be after exchange wallets are open

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the big unknown is what is the ratio between the people waiting to sell vs waiting to buy, which of course if very hard to estimate. it sure would be good to have a fully cleared market price without this fuzzy factor

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: the price on bittrex is indeed lower, but then again how many in china are using bittrex. the current theory is that most of the new demand is coming from china, so it makes sense to have a premium price on chinese exchanges vs. discount price on non-china ones
